---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "@/components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "@/components/Footer.astro";

const navLinks = [
  { href: "/", label: "Flagship" },
  { href: "#regulators", label: "Regulators" },
  { href: "#bundle", label: "The bundle" },
  { href: "#faq", label: "FAQ" },
];
const navCta = { href: "#demo", label: "See a sample bundle →" };
---

<Layout variant="evidence">
  <Nav variant="evidence" links={navLinks} cta={navCta} />

  <header class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">For compliance, legal, risk</span>
      <h1>Your AIS Program on paper. <em>And the one actually in production.</em></h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Phidea captures the ECDIS, the model decision, the adverse-decision explanation, and the policy constraint for every AI system your insurer runs. An examiner at NAIC, NY DFS, EIOPA, or ACPR asks — you export the bundle that day.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="#demo" class="btn btn-primary">See a sample bundle →</a>
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-ghost">See the platform</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <span><strong>6 frameworks</strong> mapped out of the box</span>
        <span><strong>Immutable ledger</strong> · cryptographically signed</span>
        <span><strong>Data residency</strong> pinned EU or US</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section id="regulators" style="padding: 88px 0;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">Regulator coverage</div>
        <h2>Mapped to the bulletins you actually answer to.</h2>
      </div>

      <table class="reg-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Jurisdiction</th><th>Framework</th><th>What Phidea ships</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><strong>US — NAIC</strong></td><td>Model Bulletin on AI</td><td>AIS Program evidence, third-party AI register, bias testing per LOB</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>US — NY</strong></td><td>DFS Circular Letter No. 7</td><td>ECDIS disclosure log, unfair-discrimination testing, vendor due diligence</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>US — Colorado</strong></td><td>SB21-169 (life)</td><td>Quantitative testing, protected-class proxy detection</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>EU</strong></td><td>AI Act Annex III</td><td>Risk management system, post-market monitoring, tech documentation</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>EU</strong></td><td>DORA</td><td>ICT third-party register, incident classification, resilience tests</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>EU/UK</strong></td><td>IDD, FCA Consumer Duty, ACPR</td><td>Advice-boundary classifier, distribution-chain audit trail</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="bundle" style="padding: 88px 0; background: var(--soft); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">The bundle</div>
        <h2>A clear, empirical, signed trail.</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Every AI-informed decision — the prompt, the response, the ECDIS it relied on, the policy pack that constrained it, the outcome. Cryptographically signed per entry. Format-mapped to the requesting body. One click.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="faq" style="padding: 88px 0;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="section-head">
        <div class="section-eyebrow">FAQ</div>
        <h2>Straight answers.</h2>
      </div>
      <details>
        <summary>Does Phidea see PII?</summary>
        <p>Optional. Ledger runs customer-side (on-prem or VPC). The observability layer can run in hash-only mode — no raw prompts or answers leave your boundary.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How is third-party AI covered?</summary>
        <p>Every external model call (OpenAI, Anthropic, Azure, Bedrock, vendor-hosted) is logged with provider, version, and vendor contract reference. DORA ICT third-party register exports directly from the same store.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do you handle Colorado SB21-169 bias testing?</summary>
        <p>Continuous testing against proxy variables in your live traffic, plus scheduled stress tests against synthetic personas calibrated to state demographics. Results export in the format Colorado DOI accepts.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can we run air-gapped?</summary>
        <p>Yes. Gateway and ledger ship as a container bundle. Same code path as managed SaaS. Nothing phones home.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What's the security posture?</summary>
        <p>Program designed against ISO/IEC 27001, SOC 2 Type II, and HIPAA baselines. SIG questionnaire, pen-test report, and control documentation under NDA.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="demo" style="padding: 88px 0; background: var(--soft); border-top: 1px solid var(--line);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="cta-panel" style="text-align: center; max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <h2>See a sample audit bundle.</h2>
        <p>Redacted from a real production deployment. The manifest, the signature, the adverse-decision trail, the ECDIS log. What a regulator actually receives.</p>
        <form action="https://phidea-forms.vercel.app/api/lead" method="POST" style="max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 12px;">
          <input type="hidden" name="variant" value="evidence" />
          <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="work@carrier.com" required style="padding: 14px 16px; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; font-size: 15px;" />
          <input type="text" name="carrier" placeholder="Carrier or firm" required style="padding: 14px 16px; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; font-size: 15px;" />
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" style="align-self: center;">Send me a bundle →</button>
        </form>
        <div class="cta-foot">Delivered under NDA. One business day.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .reg-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 8px; font-size: 14px; }
  .reg-table thead th { text-align: left; padding: 12px 16px; background: var(--soft); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--muted); font-weight: 600; font-size: 12px; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
  .reg-table tbody td { padding: 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); vertical-align: top; color: var(--ink-2); line-height: 1.5; }
  .reg-table tbody tr:hover td { background: var(--soft); }
  .reg-table tbody td:first-child { color: var(--ink); width: 18%; }
  .reg-table tbody td:nth-child(2) { width: 28%; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-size: 13px; color: var(--accent); }
  @media (max-width: 720px) { .reg-table { font-size: 13px; } .reg-table tbody td { padding: 12px 8px; } }
</style>
